<title>Browner: vast majority of BP spill oil collected</title>
<source>Reuters</source>
<date>2010-08-04</date>
<snippet>WASHINGTON - Most of the oil from the BP spill in the Gulf of Mexico is gone thanks to containment, burning and skimming measures, the energy adviser to ...</snippet>
<content>
        
    
WASHINGTON (Reuters) - Most of the oil from the BP spill in the Gulf of Mexico is gone thanks to containment, burning and skimming measures, the energy adviser to President Barack Obama said on Wednesday.

"The good news is that the vast majority of the oil appears to be gone," Carol Browner said on ABC's "Good Morning America."


